<task id="task_BD4A000895CB440B879A45DD261FDC07" xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.1" domains="(topic ui-d) (topic hi-d) (topic pr-d) (topic sw-d)                          (topic ut-d) (topic indexing-d)" class="- topic/topic task/task ">
  <title class="- topic/title ">Create a Flash Campaign</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Flash campaigns are designed for
	 testing Flash assets on your site. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <context id="context_92B0F426B8134B2DA0B3CC1E81C11D2D" class="- topic/section task/context ">
      <p class="- topic/p ">To use a Flash Campaign, you must upload a set of
		  .swf files that have been instrumented using the flashbox ActionScript classes
		  and Adobe Flash. These flashbox and an example of their use are available from
		  the download link under the 
		  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Display Ad
			 Campaign</uicontrol> menu item. Once you've uploaded your .swf files to the
		  Flash Campaign, all fields specified in the .swf file as dynamic become
		  editable in Target, where you can also set powerful targeting rules. 
		</p>
      <!--<p class="- topic/p ">Flashboxes and Flash campaigns can also be created
		  directly from Flash Pro with the Adobe Target extension for Flash. For details
		  see: 
		</p> 
		<ul id="ul_94F34DCFF8AC4225BC1C3E69FD9995BC" class="- topic/ul "> 
		  <li id="li_72A73EA73CE1444C93B5C8776240BEB5" class="- topic/li "> 
			 <xref href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/Extensions/TestTarget/index.html" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref ">Flash and Dreamweaver
				extension documentation</xref> 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_5678224B17284223A4C32793FA95EF11" class="- topic/li "> 
			 <xref href="http://www.adobe.com/devnet/flash/articles/fl_tnt_overview.html" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref ">Flash extension
				tutorial</xref> 
		  </li> 
		</ul>-->
      <p class="- topic/p ">
        <note class="- topic/note ">Technical documentation is included as
			 comments within the flashbox ActionScript files. 
		  </note>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To create a Flash campaign: 
		</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_6FBDD48ECCB5416791201A5130086D7C" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_8E45CBF4B70D477B8B4E1DCFABE139D4" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Campaigns</uicontrol>
			 &gt; 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Create</uicontrol> &gt;
			 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Flash</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">The Create a
			 Campaign page opens. 
		  </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_67F8171131244460BE3E36A286E035C6" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Name your campaign. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">Name the campaign something descriptive that
				you will recognize months later. 
			 </p>
          <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Example:</b> Flash Test September
				2012 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_B63988E1A1094880A50989A23A08AAF0" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Include mboxes</uicontrol> to specify
			 mboxes to include in your campaign. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">Use these locations to reinforce the content
				that you show in the Flash asset. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_752D08E1231E4E55B89450B80B4BBB79" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Set the start and end dates,
			 including time of day. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p "> The time zone is determined when you create
				your account. To change your time zone, ask your account representative. 
			 </p>
          <p class="- topic/p ">The default is set to 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">When
				  Approved</uicontrol> and 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">When
				  Deactivated</uicontrol>. This ensures that your campaign begins and lasts for
				the duration of your test. You cannot view or preview a campaign before the
				start date or after the end date. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_715A19F574134F8D8EC6CFEE57884958" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Select a priority from the Priority
			 dropdown. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_5FE0BC19A5AA403D84FF61A936640068" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Upload the .swf file. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">The flashbox name, which is embedded in the
				.swf file, appears as label after you successfully upload the .swf file. 
			 </p>
          <p class="- topic/p ">You can create additional versions of the Flash
				asset by clicking 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Create
				  Experience</uicontrol> and updating the editable portions of the .swf file. To
				make sure your new version looks good, click 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Preview</uicontrol>. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_23678042316E40AD99ED04ACD6E73F34" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the 
			 <xref href="c_About_Mboxes.xml#concept_E01933A6CEDE481BBAC25F95FE3C6FD9" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref ">conversion
				mbox</xref> and 
			 <xref href="c_Capturing_Engagement.xml#concept_DB31E18F26EA426EB7A87EAE16A477A5" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref ">success
				metrics</xref> required for your campaign strategy. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">To select an engagement metric, click 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Measure
				  Engagement</uicontrol>, then select a metric from the Engagement Metric
				dropdown. When you select an engagement metric, the name of the Measure
				Engagement tab changes to show the engagement metric you have selected. 
			 </p>
          <p class="- topic/p ">To select the action that occurs when a visitor
				encounters the specified success metric, click 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Advanced
				  Options</uicontrol> and select an action from the drop-down list. For more
				information about advanced options, see 
				<xref href="r_Success_Metric_Advanced_Options.xml#reference_03C2054D36E846DD9A7C9878E816E0C8" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Success Metric Advanced Options?></xref>.
				
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_5463F9BB45B64B129DABEBBF25A209DF" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the location where you want
			 the conversion or success metric to occur. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">If you have no conversion activity in mind,
				select 
				<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">display
				  mboxes</uicontrol> as the conversion activity. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_9349CED9368748EF9536A160DB5A167C" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Set up the segments you want to apply
			 this test to. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">For more information about segments, see 
				<xref href="c_Managing_Segment_Filters.xml#concept_DF9534D4168D46D4B109DD0D2FB57781" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref "><?xm-replace_text Managing Segment Filters?></xref>.
				
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_40F14DAABCCB46308E28B4606009ED3C" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol> or 
			 <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save &amp;
				Approve</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
